The project focuses on validating and testing Samsung SSDs (PM893, PM897, 990 Pro, PM1653) across different server environments 
to ensure performance, reliability, and compatibility and  performing firmware updates, conducting performance benchmarking by measuring 
IOPS, latency, and throughput under various workloads. and also tests the ssd features like over-provisioning, secure erase, data migration, 
and power-loss protection and creating a raid groups on that drives.



The project focuses on validating and testing the Stonefly XD-series storage systems, ensuring reliability, compatibility, 
and upgrading firmware for components such as IOMs, BMC, BIOS, and CPLD, and verifying BMC features using IPMI and Redfish. 
and check the compatibility of SAS, SATA, and NVMe drives from different vendors, and creating a raid group and LUN and mapping the LUN
masking the LUN and adding the targets.
